Tigase Messenger v2.0 brings many bigfixes and enhancements as well as new features. New features: Message Archive Support Push Notification Support Vcard Support Photos and other files easy sharing Fixes: Connectivity errors are now displayed on device to indicate and display failure conditions. When devices reconnect to servers they will synchronize messages using XEP 0313 Message Archive Management if enabled on both device and server. Fixed crash from missing data when updating avatar. Fixed crash on processing incoming stanza while disconnecting or opening chat with text unable to parse to a URL. Fixed crash when receiving messages in MUC while chat was open. Improved badge refresh rate. Fixed crash while viewing file preview and download file size set to unlimited. Fixed delay between detection of disconnection and delivery of push notification. Fixed visual bug displaying large text on smaller device in some setting menus. Fixed issue where delivery receipt messages could bounce back as errors. Application now updates information from roster pushes correctly. Modified dispatch queue usage to prevent a race condition when creating a chat from device. Improved JID comparison to prevent chats with same JID and different content showing in seperate chats in recent chat list. Improved database access and fixed concurrency issues from db timeout issues. Improved stability of application after download failure due to connectivity issues. Fixed crashing when updating roster views. Fixed crash when opening MUC while client is fetching messages from MUC server. Fixed issue where recent screen could hang during message synchronization.
Many bug fixes and minor improvements related to account creation and reconnection issues.
